                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable K</hi> 182.) I took the prisoner—I told him it was for stealing a coat—he said, "You must prove it"—I said, "It is pawned in the name of Smith"—he said, "Smith knows nothing about it; Green took it, and I pawned it"—I said, "The prosecutor has re<lb></lb>ceived a letter with the duplicate, is it your writing?"—he said, "Yes, I sent it."</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I took the coat as a pattern round to the trade—Green went with me—I stood outside, while he took it into shops, and then he went away with it—the letter I never wrote nor sent—I never pawned the coat.</p>
